  "title": "How to make show-more button in hierarchicalMenu?",
  "body": "I tried like this:\r\n```\r\nvar CustomHierarchicalMenuWidgetOptions = {\r\n    container: '#hierarchical-categories',\r\n    attributes: ['hierarchicalCategories.lvl0', 'hierarchicalCategories.lvl1', 'hierarchicalCategories.lvl2', 'hierarchicalCategories.lvl3', 'hierarchicalCategories.lvl4'],\r\n    limit: 100, \r\n    showParentLevel: true,\r\n    autoHideContainer: true,\r\n    templates: {\r\n      header: getHeader('Kategorie'),\r\n      item: '<a href=\"{{url}}\" class=\"facet-item \"><span class=\"facet-name\"><span class=\"icon\"></span><span>{{label}}</span></span></a>'\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n  function renderFn3(HierarchicalMenuRenderingOptions) {\r\n    var container = HierarchicalMenuRenderingOptions.widgetParams.container;\r\n    console.log(HierarchicalMenuRenderingOptions)\r\n    console.log(container)\r\n  }\r\n  var makeHierarchicalMenu= instantsearch.connectors.connectHierarchicalMenu(renderFn3);\r\n  \r\n  var  customHierarchicalMenu = makeHierarchicalMenu(CustomHierarchicalMenuWidgetOptions);\r\n  search.addWidget(customHierarchicalMenu);\r\n```\r\nconsole.log(HierarchicalMenuRenderingOptions) looks nice, but it does not render anyway. I dont have idea why. \r\nLink to complete example is 404..\r\nI don't have idea what to do next after render custom widget anyway. Can you help?\r\n",
